[^1747]: The Dutch established in the Moluccas employ a similar method to keep their subjects in servitude.
> “They take great care,” says Labillardière, “not to teach them their mother tongue, so as not to be understood when they converse among themselves.”
*Voyage à la recherche de La Pérouse*, ch. VII, volume I, page 355.
